Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.77,0:00:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}June 19, my first meeting\Nwith Franz Bonaparta.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.70,0:00:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}RF-17-9.\NHe's a very quiet man.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.54,0:00:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He behaved elegantly\Nand wore a suit.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.11,0:00:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In the afternoon, he gathered\Nthe children for a book reading.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.76,0:00:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you want to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.66,0:00:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,To the border.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.90,0:00:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Which border?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.23,0:00:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The Czech border.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.63,0:00:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.90,0:00:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.71,0:01:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In the afternoon, he gathered\Nthe children for a book reading.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.38,0:01:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A very strange mansion...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.69,0:01:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Red Rose Mansion...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.39,0:01:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}P-Brevnov W..{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.89,0:01:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A steeple to the left...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.76,0:01:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A weather vane\Nto the right...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.63,0:01:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Human dignity...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.56,0:01:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Experiment...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.27,0:01:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Amazing experiments...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.54,0:01:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Deprivation of dignity...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.00,0:01:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.34,0:01:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.77,0:01:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I said,\N"What country are you from?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.91,0:01:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. I'm Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.54,0:01:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if a Japanese man\Nwould like this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.72,0:01:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat this.\NIt's leftover from my lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.09,0:01:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.72,0:01:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.29,0:01:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like you're\Ngoing to collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.33,0:01:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife has been nagging me\Nto go on a diet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.36,0:01:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I won't hesitate.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.27,0:01:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Eat, eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.17,0:02:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't be able to last\Nthe long journey if you don't eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.18,0:02:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to finish this journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.61,0:03:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.31,0:03:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You let him go?\NYou just let Tenma go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.24,0:03:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.95,0:03:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you stop him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.81,0:03:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that you can't stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.72,0:03:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.09,0:04:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially since Eva Heinemann\Nis now missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.32,0:04:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a race against the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.13,0:04:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why Tenma escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.87,0:04:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That lawyer called Baul
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.04,0:04:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is probably the same man who\Ntried to kill me at my clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.81,0:04:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He was planning to take my father's\Nnotebook by getting close to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.42,0:04:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That notebook must be\Npretty important.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.99,0:04:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.46,0:04:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.99,0:04:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The place where\NTenma is headed...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.16,0:04:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The Red Rose Mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.56,0:04:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.06,0:04:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,My father's notebook is filled\Nwith unintelligible descriptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.77,0:04:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think that part is code.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.40,0:04:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Red Rose Mansion,\NP-Brevnov W...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.91,0:04:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,"P" stands for "Prague"\Nand "W' means "west."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.65,0:04:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The Prague suburbs to\Nthe west of Brevnov.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.18,0:05:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's somewhere you can see a steeple to\Nthe left and a weather vane to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.22,0:05:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.59,0:05:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that\Nthere's a witness
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.43,0:05:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who will get us closer to solving\Nthis case at that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.93,0:05:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But at this point...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.67,0:05:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.43,0:05:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.97,0:05:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,An entry in the notebook said that children\Nwould gather for recitals in the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.41,0:05:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Those children are\Nour witnesses, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.05,0:05:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Vardemann...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.81,0:05:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I scolded you for\Nletting Tenma go,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.29,0:05:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but had I been in the same position,\NI'd have done the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.93,0:05:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.30,0:05:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.74,0:05:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I lived in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.87,0:05:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.04,0:06:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Welcome home{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.22,0:06:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.32,0:06:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.59,0:06:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.59,0:06:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that\Nyou should give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.03,0:06:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You get lost\Nevery time you try.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.43,0:06:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I'll remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.37,0:06:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,My brother talked to me\Nat that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.44,0:06:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When he was taken from\Nthe "Three Frogs"...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.07,0:06:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What he passed along the way\Nand where he was taken...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.35,0:06:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When he passed the station,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.61,0:06:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a streetcar ran along the riverside\Nas he watched the town to his left...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.59,0:06:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.63,0:06:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.30,0:06:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't keep secrets from him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.97,0:07:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.31,0:07:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.71,0:07:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,N-Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.89,0:07:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?\NNotice anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.29,0:07:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.63,0:07:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.86,0:07:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't be able to remember a\Nconversation from such a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.57,0:07:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.27,0:08:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A weather vane to the right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.32,0:08:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A church steeple to the left...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.92,0:08:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.08,0:08:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The Red Rose Mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.19,0:08:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.85,0:08:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.69,0:09:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But. ..I know this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.04,0:09:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm afraid"...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.49,0:09:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.17,0:09:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like the door just\Nemerged out of the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.24,0:10:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.71,0:10:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.58,0:10:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina ! Nina ! Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.78,0:10:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.29,0:10:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You demon! You demon !\NYou demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.90,0:10:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The demon is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.76,0:11:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.30,0:11:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Mr. Lipsky.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.74,0:11:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you have an audience?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.64,0:11:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I was terrible, as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.08,0:11:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're such\Nwonderful dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.51,0:11:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The one I'm making right now\Nis even better.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.22,0:11:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to see it soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.09,0:11:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show it to you\Nright after I finish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.86,0:11:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time to go to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.06,0:11:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.13,0:11:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I can't make enough\Njust on dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.17,0:12:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for staying here\Nfor so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.84,0:12:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It's all right.\NDon't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.11,0:12:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Lipsky,\NI want to ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.01,0:12:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.92,0:12:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Three months ago, you found me\Nunconscious and took me to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.26,0:12:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.92,0:12:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why were you\Nat that mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.26,0:12:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nina! Nina!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.63,0:12:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nina!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.60,0:12:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Answer me, Nina! Nina!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.17,0:12:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What happened?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.28,0:12:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,When I go to that mansion,\NI get ideas for my stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.02,0:12:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I say this?\NUmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.39,0:12:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But right now,\Nrather than that mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.26,0:12:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's all right.\NAnyway, don't be shy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.23,0:13:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can stay here\Nas long as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.70,0:13:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.37,0:13:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.14,0:13:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.\NShould you be up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.84,0:13:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.78,0:13:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So this room is where\Nyour dolls are born.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.82,0:13:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have an audience,\Nthough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.42,0:13:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your play about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.56,0:14:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the story of a demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.26,0:14:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.90,0:14:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing. Continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.00,0:14:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A demon sets out on a journey in search\Nof a dragon that will destroy the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.00,0:14:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,On the way, he nearly dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.77,0:14:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But a boy who's passing by\Nsaves his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.61,0:14:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When the boy realizes who he's\Nsaved, he chases after the demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.29,0:14:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of his journey,\Nhe finds the demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.59,0:14:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And with a knife in his hand,\Nkills the demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.56,0:14:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's interesting,\Nbut it isn't popular at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.13,0:14:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.57,0:14:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that I would do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.44,0:14:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.81,0:14:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I would do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.11,0:14:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But I mustn't let him do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.62,0:15:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.82,0:15:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A human would...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.09,0:15:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,save that demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.59,0:15:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.06,0:15:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that he'd like this story.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.59,0:15:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"He?"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.80,0:15:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This shelf...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.17,0:15:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all picture books.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.93,0:15:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Jakub Farobek. .. Klaus Poppe...\NEmile Scherbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.61,0:15:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Nameless Monster...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.71,0:15:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.08,0:15:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote many picture books.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.22,0:15:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Jakub Farobek. .. Klaus Poppe...\NEmile Scherbe...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.39,0:15:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all pseudonyms\Nfor the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.36,0:15:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The person called\NFranz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.56,0:15:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz. ..Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.37,0:15:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}People can become\Nwhatever they want to be.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.54,0:16:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't a brilliant child,\Nso I was thrown out of the recitals.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.48,0:16:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Recitals?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.02,0:16:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He held recitals at\Nthe Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.32,0:16:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a student there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.59,0:16:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew what\Nhe was trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.07,0:16:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"A deal. Let's make a deal"'\Nsaid the demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.47,0:16:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,"No, never"' said the man\Nwith the big eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.41,0:16:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,"Sure. Let's make a deal"'\Nsaid the man with the big mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.71,0:16:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The man with the big mouth's yard\Nbecame a flower garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.42,0:16:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The man with the big eyes was\Nvery hungry because he was very poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.23,0:16:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The man with the big mouth\Nhad so much fun everyday.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.23,0:16:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He was very full from eating the fruit\Nharvested from his garden,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.50,0:17:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,so he didn't realize that\Nhis flower garden was withering.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.71,0:17:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The man with the big mouth\Ncried and cried
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.58,0:17:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in the garden that\Nwould never grow again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.92,0:17:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"I shouldn't have made a deal\Nwith that demon." he cried.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.22,0:17:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The big-eyed person\Nwas dying of hunger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.36,0:17:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As the tears fell,\Nhe cried,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.56,0:17:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,"I should have made\Na deal with the demon"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.17,0:17:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,"A deal. Let's make a deal."\Nthe demon said.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.94,0:17:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jakub Farobek's
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.01,0:17:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Jakub Farobek's {\i1}The Man with the\NBig Eyes, the Man with the Big Mouth.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.91,0:17:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd gather every Friday\Nat 3 PM for the recital.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.92,0:17:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd gather around him and listen,\Nhe'd read to us in a kind voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.79,0:17:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In a kind voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.93,0:18:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A very kind and gentle voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.07,0:18:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And once he was done\Nreading a story, he'd ask them...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.87,0:18:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"The meaning of this story. .."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.41,0:18:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You understand it don't you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.98,0:18:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.58,0:18:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I also understood after\Nreading it several times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.45,0:18:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he'd take the next book.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.86,0:18:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Klaus Poppe's\N{\i1}The God of Peace.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.36,0:18:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's read this one next.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.04,0:18:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if I've come here\Nfor the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.38,0:18:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Though it's taken quite some time...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.62,0:18:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,all my memories have come together.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.36,0:19:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of Peace\Nwas very busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.19,0:19:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He blew his trumpet every day. He\Ndidn't have the time to look in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.40,0:19:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of Peace's trumpet\Nmade everyone happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.00,0:19:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of Peace was very busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.61,0:19:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He poured the mysterious water. He\Ndidn't have the time to look in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.08,0:19:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The mysterious water made\Nthe mountains green,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.05,0:19:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,made the fields grow,\Nand made fields of flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.42,0:19:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of Peace was very busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.22,0:19:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave everyone names. He didn't\Nhave the time to look in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.06,0:19:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is Otto.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.39,0:19:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is Hans.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.73,0:19:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is Thomas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.50,0:19:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.60,0:19:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In appreciation,\NJohan gave the God a lovely hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.64,0:19:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The God was very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.31,0:19:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted to see what\Nhe looked like with the hat on
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.81,0:20:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and, for the first time,\Nhe stood before a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.22,0:20:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was a demon\Nreflected in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.49,0:20:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The demon said,\N"You are me and I am you."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.60,0:20:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,"What should I do?"\Nsaid the god.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.90,0:20:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,"No one can live in peace\Nwith a demon here."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.40,0:20:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"What should I do?\NWhat should I do?"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.60,0:20:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The troubled God...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.97,0:20:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know\Nwhat he did next?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.81,0:20:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.58,0:20:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know?\NDo you know what the God did?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.32,0:20:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.12,0:20:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We finally meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.36,0:20:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm back. Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.20,0:20:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.54,0:20:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Even you couldn't tell us apart,\Ncould you, Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.97,0:21:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She is me and I am her.\NYou are me and I am you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.98,0:21:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.41,0:21:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Where we came from\Nand where we're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.22,0:21:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The weather's nice outside,\NMother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.31,0:21:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything will be in flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.57,0:21:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.77,0:21:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The God...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.88,0:22:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,points a gun\Nto his forehead...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.80,0:22:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoot me.
